CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, pg. 3, reads: "Undamaged - Construction on this home, which is approximately 350 yards from Alonzo Sander' property, was completed a few days before the fire of undetermined origin damaged the latter's $13,000 home. This new home was not damaged. Sanders believes his home was set afire by a bigot or bigots who do not want Negroes living in area. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ranch style brick house with light colored front door, six front windows, and chimney, on lot with long driveway and small tree front right on Christy Road in Eighty Four, Pennsylvania
